{"documentCount":64,"nextId":64,"documentIds":{"0":"ai/","1":"ai/#overview","2":"ai/#configuration","3":"ai/#provider-behavior","4":"ai/#what-gets-sent","5":"ai/#troubleshooting","6":"cli/","7":"cli/#commands","8":"cli/#nova-ask","9":"cli/#how-it-works","10":"configuration/","11":"configuration/#location","12":"configuration/#file-lifecycle","13":"configuration/#defaults","14":"configuration/#reference","15":"configuration/#reference-general","16":"configuration/#reference-status-bar","17":"configuration/#reference-themefont","18":"configuration/#reference-themecolors","19":"configuration/#reference-themecursor","20":"configuration/#reference-keybindings","21":"configuration/#reference-ai","22":"development/","23":"development/#build-nova","24":"development/#code-map","25":"development/#build-the-docs-site","26":"development/#ci-notes","27":"/","28":"/#start-here","29":"/#reference","30":"/#internals","31":"/#help","32":"installation/","33":"installation/#installation","34":"installation/#installation-homebrew","35":"installation/#installation-winget-windows","36":"installation/#installation-scoop-windows","37":"installation/#installation-aur-arch-linux","38":"installation/#installation-apt-debianubuntu","39":"installation/#installation-dnfrpm-fedorarhel","40":"internals-osc/","41":"internals-osc/#private-nova-osc-channel","42":"internals-osc/#private-nova-osc-channel-command-askai","43":"internals-osc/#osc-7-current-working-directory","44":"internals-osc/#osc-8-hyperlinks","45":"keybindings/","46":"keybindings/#binding-syntax","47":"keybindings/#actions","48":"keybindings/#defaults","49":"keybindings/#fixed-shortcuts","50":"keybindings/#fixed-shortcuts-split-pane","51":"keybindings/#fixed-shortcuts-font-size","52":"keybindings/#fixed-shortcuts-search","53":"keybindings/#notes","54":"quickstart/","55":"quickstart/#first-run","56":"quickstart/#editing-settings","57":"quickstart/#command-palette","58":"quickstart/#ai-overlay","59":"troubleshooting/","60":"troubleshooting/#macos-nova-is-damaged-and-cant-be-opened","61":"troubleshooting/#settings-keep-resetting","62":"troubleshooting/#nova-ask-must-be-run-inside-nova","63":"troubleshooting/#ai-errors"},"fieldIds":{"title":0,"headings":1,"text":2},"fieldLength":{"0":[1,8,114],"1":[3,1,1],"2":[3,1,1],"3":[4,2,1],"4":[5,3,1],"5":[3,1,1],"6":[1,6,67],"7":[3,1,1],"8":[4,2,1],"9":[5,3,1],"10":[1,15,221],"11":[3,1,1],"12":[4,2,1],"13":[3,1,1],"14":[3,1,1],"15":[4,2,1],"16":[5,3,1],"17":[5,3,1],"18":[5,3,1],"19":[5,3,1],"20":[4,2,1],"21":[4,2,1],"22":[1,9,87],"23":[4,2,1],"24":[4,2,1],"25":[6,4,1],"26":[4,2,1],"27":[2,5,16],"28":[5,2,1],"29":[4,1,1],"30":[4,1,1],"31":[4,1,1],"32":[2,16,64],"33":[4,1,1],"34":[4,1,1],"35":[6,3,1],"36":[6,3,1],"37":[7,4,1],"38":[7,4,1],"39":[8,5,1],"40":[2,13,105],"41":[6,4,1],"42":[6,3,1],"43":[7,5,1],"44":[5,3,1],"45":[1,12,201],"46":[4,2,1],"47":[3,1,1],"48":[3,1,1],"49":[4,2,1],"50":[4,2,1],"51":[4,2,1],"52":[3,1,1],"53":[3,1,1],"54":[1,8,94],"55":[4,2,1],"56":[4,2,1],"57":[4,2,1],"58":[4,2,1],"59":[1,20,106],"60":[12,10,1],"61":[5,3,1],"62":[9,7,1],"63":[4,2,1]},"averageFieldLength":[4.109374999999999,3.78125,17.640625],"storedFields":{"0":{"title":"AI","id":"ai/","text":"Overview\nNova’s AI features live in the UI (Ask AI and Explain Error). They use:\n\nYour question\nTerminal context extracted from the last command output\n\nAI is optional. If api_key is empty, requests fail with a clear error.\nConfiguration\nSettings live under [ai] in settings.toml:\n[ai]\nprovider = &quot;anthropic&quot;  # or &quot;openai&quot;\nmodel = &quot;claude-haiku-4-5-20251001&quot;\napi_key = &quot;&quot;\n# base_url = &quot;https://api.anthropic.com&quot;  # optional\n\nFields:\n\nprovider: anthropic or openai\nmodel: Provider-specific model name\napi_key: Required\nbase_url: Optional override (useful for proxies)\n\nProvider Behavior\nAnthropic:\n\nDefault base_url is https://api.anthropic.com.\n\nOpenAI:\n\nDefault base_url is https://api.openai.com/v1/.\nIf you set base_url without a trailing /, Nova adds it.\n\nWhat Gets Sent\nNova builds a system prompt including OS and shell, and includes terminal context from the last output.\nTerminal context is extracted by scanning for the prompt marker and collecting the lines after it, trimming empty lines.\nTroubleshooting\n\n“No API key configured”: Set [ai].api_key in Settings or settings.toml.\nModel errors: Confirm the model name exists for the selected provider.\nProxy/base URL issues: Ensure base_url includes scheme and is reachable.\n\n"},"1":{"title":"AI > Overview","id":"ai/#overview","text":""},"2":{"title":"AI > Configuration","id":"ai/#configuration","text":""},"3":{"title":"AI > Provider Behavior","id":"ai/#provider-behavior","text":""},"4":{"title":"AI > What Gets Sent","id":"ai/#what-gets-sent","text":""},"5":{"title":"AI > Troubleshooting","id":"ai/#troubleshooting","text":""},"6":{"title":"CLI","id":"cli/","text":"Commands\nNova includes a small CLI surface:\n\nnova help: Show usage\nnova ask [preset...]: Open the Ask AI modal in the running Nova app\n\nnova ask\nnova ask is not a standalone AI client.\nIt must be run inside Nova. Nova sets NOVA_TERMINAL=1 for its child shells; the CLI checks that environment variable.\nExamples:\nnova ask\n\nnova ask explain this error\n\nIf you’re not in Nova, you’ll see:\nerror: &#039;nova ask&#039; must be run inside Nova terminal\n\nHow It Works\nThe CLI emits a private OSC sequence that Nova’s terminal parser understands.\nDetails are documented in OSC Integration.\n"},"7":{"title":"CLI > Commands","id":"cli/#commands","text":""},"8":{"title":"CLI > nova ask","id":"cli/#nova-ask","text":""},"9":{"title":"CLI > How It Works","id":"cli/#how-it-works","text":""},"10":{"title":"Configuration","id":"configuration/","text":"Location\nNova stores settings at settings.toml under your OS config directory:\n\nWindows: %APPDATA%\\nova\\settings.toml\nmacOS: ~/Library/Application Support/nova/settings.toml\nLinux: ~/.config/nova/settings.toml\n\nInternally, this is dirs::config_dir().join(&quot;nova&quot;).join(&quot;settings.toml&quot;).\nFile Lifecycle\n\nIf settings.toml does not exist, Nova writes an embedded default config.\nIf settings.toml exists but TOML parsing fails, Nova overwrites it with defaults.\n\nThis means a malformed edit can be “repaired” by reset-to-default (but you may lose changes).\nDefaults\nNova ships embedded defaults (slightly different on macOS).\nNon-macOS default excerpt:\n[general]\neditor = &quot;nano&quot;\nbell = &quot;none&quot;\n\n[status-bar]\nvisible = true\ndate-format = &quot;%b %d&quot;\ntime-format = &quot;%H:%M:%S&quot;\n\n[theme.font]\nsize = 16\nfamily = &quot;FiraCode Nerd Font&quot;\n\n[theme.colors]\nbackground = &quot;#0D0D0D&quot;\nforeground = &quot;#E5E5E5&quot;\naccent = &quot;#3ECF8E&quot;\nforeground-muted = &quot;#666666&quot;\nborder = &quot;#FFFFFF12&quot;\ncursor = &quot;#3ECF8E&quot;\n\n[theme.cursor]\nstyle = &quot;underline&quot;\nblink = false\n\n[keybindings]\nnew-tab = &quot;ctrl+t&quot;\nclose-tab = &quot;ctrl+w&quot;\nnext-tab = &quot;ctrl+tab&quot;\nprev-tab = &quot;ctrl+shift+tab&quot;\npaste = &quot;ctrl+v&quot;\ncopy = &quot;ctrl+shift+c&quot;\nopen-palette = &quot;ctrl+k&quot;\n\n[ai]\nprovider = &quot;anthropic&quot;\nmodel = &quot;claude-haiku-4-5-20251001&quot;\napi_key = &quot;&quot;\n\nReference\n[general]\n\neditor (string): External editor command.\nbell (string): One of none, audio, blink.\nshells (array of strings, optional): If set and non-empty, Nova uses this list instead of auto-detect.\nwindow-controls (string): One of traffic-lights or system.\nscrollback (integer, optional): Maximum scrollback lines per pane. Defaults to 10000.\n\nExample:\n[general]\neditor = &quot;code -w&quot;\nbell = &quot;none&quot;\nshells = [&quot;zsh&quot;, &quot;bash&quot;]\nwindow-controls = &quot;system&quot;\n\n[status-bar]\n\nvisible (bool)\ndate-format (string)\ntime-format (string)\n\nExample:\n[status-bar]\nvisible = true\ndate-format = &quot;%Y-%m-%d&quot;\ntime-format = &quot;%H:%M&quot;\n\n[theme.font]\n\nsize (number)\nfamily (string)\n\nExample:\n[theme.font]\nsize = 15\nfamily = &quot;FiraCode Nerd Font&quot;\n\n[theme.colors]\nAll values are hex strings.\n\n#RRGGBB is supported.\n#RRGGBBAA is supported (alpha channel).\n\nKeys:\n\nbackground\nforeground\naccent\nforeground-muted\nborder\ncursor\n\nExample:\n[theme.colors]\nbackground = &quot;#0D0D0D&quot;\nforeground = &quot;#E5E5E5&quot;\naccent = &quot;#3ECF8E&quot;\nforeground-muted = &quot;#666666&quot;\nborder = &quot;#FFFFFF12&quot;\ncursor = &quot;#3ECF8E&quot;\n\n[theme.cursor]\nstyle = &quot;underline&quot;\nblink = true\n\n[ai]\nprovider = &quot;anthropic&quot;\nmodel = &quot;claude-haiku-4-5-20251001&quot;\napi_key = &quot;&quot;\n\n[theme.cursor]\n\nstyle (string): Cursor shape. One of block, beam, underline.\nblink (bool): Whether the cursor blinks.\n\nExample:\n[theme.cursor]\nstyle = &quot;underline&quot;\nblink = true\n\n[keybindings]\nSee Keybindings for syntax and examples.\nKeys:\n\nnew-tab\nclose-tab\nnext-tab\nprev-tab\npaste\ncopy\nopen-palette\n\n[ai]\nSee AI for behavior and troubleshooting.\n\nprovider (string): anthropic or openai\nmodel (string)\napi_key (string)\nbase_url (string, optional): Override API base URL (useful for proxies).\n\nExample:\n[ai]\nprovider = &quot;openai&quot;\nmodel = &quot;gpt-4.1-mini&quot;\napi_key = &quot;...&quot;\nbase_url = &quot;https://api.openai.com/v1/&quot;\n\n"},"11":{"title":"Configuration > Location","id":"configuration/#location","text":""},"12":{"title":"Configuration > File Lifecycle","id":"configuration/#file-lifecycle","text":""},"13":{"title":"Configuration > Defaults","id":"configuration/#defaults","text":""},"14":{"title":"Configuration > Reference","id":"configuration/#reference","text":""},"15":{"title":"Configuration > [general]","id":"configuration/#reference-general","text":""},"16":{"title":"Configuration > [status-bar]","id":"configuration/#reference-status-bar","text":""},"17":{"title":"Configuration > [theme.font]","id":"configuration/#reference-themefont","text":""},"18":{"title":"Configuration > [theme.colors]","id":"configuration/#reference-themecolors","text":""},"19":{"title":"Configuration > [theme.cursor]","id":"configuration/#reference-themecursor","text":""},"20":{"title":"Configuration > [keybindings]","id":"configuration/#reference-keybindings","text":""},"21":{"title":"Configuration > [ai]","id":"configuration/#reference-ai","text":""},"22":{"title":"Development","id":"development/","text":"Build Nova\nNova uses Rust (stable, edition 2024).\ngit clone https://github.com/pmqueiroz/nova.git\ncd nova\ncargo build --release\n\nBinary output:\n./target/release/nova\n\nFor local iteration:\ncargo run\n\nCode Map\nHigh-level ownership:\n\nsrc/core/: config, grid model, ANSI/VTE state, AI client\nsrc/sys/: PTY bridge, platform I/O, terminal parser\nsrc/ui/: iced application, components, theme\n\nBuild The Docs Site\nDocs live in docs/ and are built with @docmd/core.\nFrom the repo root:\ncd docs\nbun install\nbun run dev\n\nBuild output goes to docs/dist:\ncd docs\nbun run build\n\nCI Notes\nThe main CI enforces formatting and linting.\nBefore opening a PR:\ncargo fmt\ncargo clippy\ncargo build\n\n"},"23":{"title":"Development > Build Nova","id":"development/#build-nova","text":""},"24":{"title":"Development > Code Map","id":"development/#code-map","text":""},"25":{"title":"Development > Build The Docs Site","id":"development/#build-the-docs-site","text":""},"26":{"title":"Development > CI Notes","id":"development/#ci-notes","text":""},"27":{"title":"Nova Documentation","id":"/","text":"Start Here\n\nInstallation\nQuickstart\n\nReference\n\nConfiguration\nKeybindings\nAI\nCLI\n\nInternals\n\nOSC Integration\nDevelopment\n\nHelp\n\nTroubleshooting\n\n"},"28":{"title":"Nova Documentation > Start Here","id":"/#start-here","text":""},"29":{"title":"Nova Documentation > Reference","id":"/#reference","text":""},"30":{"title":"Nova Documentation > Internals","id":"/#internals","text":""},"31":{"title":"Nova Documentation > Help","id":"/#help","text":""},"32":{"title":"Nova Docs","id":"installation/","text":"Installation\nHomebrew\n\nmacOSLinuxbrew install --cask pmqueiroz/tap/nova\n\nbrew install pmqueiroz/tap/nova\n\nWinget (Windows)\nwinget install pmqueiroz.Nova\n\nScoop (Windows)\nscoop bucket add pmqueiroz https://github.com/pmqueiroz/scoop-bucket\nscoop install nova\n\nAUR (Arch Linux)\nyay -S nova-bin\n\nAPT (Debian/Ubuntu)\ncurl -fsSL https://pmqueiroz.github.io/apt-repo/KEY.gpg | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/nova.gpg\necho &quot;deb [trusted=yes arch=amd64] https://pmqueiroz.github.io/apt-repo stable main&quot; \\\n  | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/nova.list\nsudo apt update &amp;&amp; sudo apt install nova\n\nDNF/RPM (Fedora/RHEL)\nsudo curl -fsSL https://pmqueiroz.github.io/rpm-repo/nova.repo \\\n  -o /etc/yum.repos.d/nova.repo\nsudo dnf install nova\n\n"},"33":{"title":"Nova Docs > Installation","id":"installation/#installation","text":""},"34":{"title":"Nova Docs > Homebrew","id":"installation/#installation-homebrew","text":""},"35":{"title":"Nova Docs > Winget (Windows)","id":"installation/#installation-winget-windows","text":""},"36":{"title":"Nova Docs > Scoop (Windows)","id":"installation/#installation-scoop-windows","text":""},"37":{"title":"Nova Docs > AUR (Arch Linux)","id":"installation/#installation-aur-arch-linux","text":""},"38":{"title":"Nova Docs > APT (Debian/Ubuntu)","id":"installation/#installation-apt-debianubuntu","text":""},"39":{"title":"Nova Docs > DNF/RPM (Fedora/RHEL)","id":"installation/#installation-dnfrpm-fedorarhel","text":""},"40":{"title":"OSC Integration","id":"internals-osc/","text":"Nova supports a small set of OSC (Operating System Command) sequences.\nSome are standard-ish (OSC 7, OSC 8), and one is a Nova-private channel used by nova CLI commands.\nPrivate Nova OSC Channel\nNova uses a private OSC code 777.\nFormat:\nESC ] 777 ; &lt;command&gt; [ ; &lt;arg&gt; ... ] BEL\n\nWhere:\n\nESC is \\x1b\nTerminator is BEL (\\x07)\n\nCommand: ask_ai\nnova ask sends:\nESC ] 777 ; ask_ai [ ; &lt;preset_b64&gt; ] BEL\n\nIf a preset is provided, it is base64-encoded (standard base64, no newlines).\nExamples:\nNo preset:\n\\x1b]777;ask_ai\\x07\n\nWith preset &quot;hello&quot; (base64: aGVsbG8=):\n\\x1b]777;ask_ai;aGVsbG8=\\x07\n\nOSC 7: Current Working Directory\nNova parses OSC 7 to track a working directory string.\nIt expects a file:// URL or ssh:// host-like value.\nThis is used for display/state and may differ from your shell’s own concept of PWD.\nOSC 8: Hyperlinks\nNova parses OSC 8 URIs and stores the “current” URI while rendering.\nThis enables link hover behavior.\n"},"41":{"title":"OSC Integration > Private Nova OSC Channel","id":"internals-osc/#private-nova-osc-channel","text":""},"42":{"title":"OSC Integration > Command: ask_ai","id":"internals-osc/#private-nova-osc-channel-command-askai","text":""},"43":{"title":"OSC Integration > OSC 7: Current Working Directory","id":"internals-osc/#osc-7-current-working-directory","text":""},"44":{"title":"OSC Integration > OSC 8: Hyperlinks","id":"internals-osc/#osc-8-hyperlinks","text":""},"45":{"title":"Keybindings","id":"keybindings/","text":"Binding Syntax\nBindings are strings like ctrl+t or ctrl+shift+tab.\nSupported modifiers:\n\nctrl\nshift\nalt (alias: option)\ncmd (aliases: command, meta, super)\n\nSupported keys:\n\ntab\nAny single character (like t, w, c, v, k)\n\nExamples:\n[keybindings]\nnew-tab = &quot;ctrl+t&quot;\nclose-tab = &quot;ctrl+w&quot;\nnext-tab = &quot;ctrl+tab&quot;\nprev-tab = &quot;ctrl+shift+tab&quot;\ncopy = &quot;ctrl+shift+c&quot;\npaste = &quot;ctrl+v&quot;\nopen-palette = &quot;ctrl+k&quot;\n\nActions\nThese keys live under [keybindings] in settings.toml:\n\nnew-tab\nclose-tab\nnext-tab\nprev-tab\ncopy\npaste\nopen-palette\n\nDefaults\nDefaults differ on macOS vs other platforms.\nNon-macOS (defaults):\n[keybindings]\nnew-tab = &quot;ctrl+t&quot;\nclose-tab = &quot;ctrl+w&quot;\nnext-tab = &quot;ctrl+tab&quot;\nprev-tab = &quot;ctrl+shift+tab&quot;\npaste = &quot;ctrl+v&quot;\ncopy = &quot;ctrl+shift+c&quot;\nopen-palette = &quot;ctrl+k&quot;\n\nmacOS (defaults):\n[keybindings]\nnew-tab = &quot;cmd+t&quot;\nclose-tab = &quot;cmd+w&quot;\nnext-tab = &quot;ctrl+tab&quot;\nprev-tab = &quot;ctrl+shift+tab&quot;\npaste = &quot;cmd+v&quot;\ncopy = &quot;cmd+c&quot;\nopen-palette = &quot;cmd+k&quot;\n\nFixed Shortcuts\nThese shortcuts are hardcoded and cannot be changed via settings.toml.\nSplit Pane\n\n\n\nAction\nmacOS\nOther\n\n\n\n\nOpen split pane\nCmd+Shift+T\nCtrl+Shift+T\n\n\nClose split pane\nCmd+Shift+W\nCtrl+Shift+W\n\n\n\nWhen a split pane is open, close-tab (Cmd+W / Ctrl+W) closes the active pane instead of the entire tab.\nThe divider between panes is draggable. Hover over it to see a resize cursor, then click and drag to adjust the split ratio. Grids resize when you release the mouse. The ratio is clamped to 10%–90%.\nFont Size\n\n\n\nAction\nmacOS\nOther\n\n\n\n\nIncrease font size\nCmd+= or Cmd++\nCtrl+= or Ctrl++\n\n\nDecrease font size\nCmd+-\nCtrl+-\n\n\nReset font size\nCmd+0\nCtrl+0\n\n\n\nFont size steps snap to even numbers (e.g. 15 → 16 → 18 → 20). Range: 8–72. Reset returns to the size that was configured at app start.\nSearch\n\n\n\nAction\nmacOS\nOther\n\n\n\n\nOpen search bar\nCmd+F\nCtrl+F\n\n\nNext match\nEnter\nEnter\n\n\nPrevious match\nShift+Enter\nShift+Enter\n\n\nClose search\nEscape\nEscape\n\n\n\nSearch is case-insensitive and covers both the scrollback buffer and the visible terminal rows. The current match is highlighted in yellow; other matches are dimly highlighted. The match count is shown in the search bar (e.g. 3 / 15). Searching closes automatically when switching tabs.\nNotes\n\nIf open-palette is invalid, Nova falls back to ctrl+k.\n\n"},"46":{"title":"Keybindings > Binding Syntax","id":"keybindings/#binding-syntax","text":""},"47":{"title":"Keybindings > Actions","id":"keybindings/#actions","text":""},"48":{"title":"Keybindings > Defaults","id":"keybindings/#defaults","text":""},"49":{"title":"Keybindings > Fixed Shortcuts","id":"keybindings/#fixed-shortcuts","text":""},"50":{"title":"Keybindings > Split Pane","id":"keybindings/#fixed-shortcuts-split-pane","text":""},"51":{"title":"Keybindings > Font Size","id":"keybindings/#fixed-shortcuts-font-size","text":""},"52":{"title":"Keybindings > Search","id":"keybindings/#fixed-shortcuts-search","text":""},"53":{"title":"Keybindings > Notes","id":"keybindings/#notes","text":""},"54":{"title":"Quickstart","id":"quickstart/","text":"First Run\nOn first launch, Nova creates a settings file if it doesn’t exist.\nConfig file path is:\n\nWindows: %APPDATA%\\nova\\settings.toml\nmacOS: ~/Library/Application Support/nova/settings.toml\nLinux: ~/.config/nova/settings.toml\n\nEditing Settings\nNova reads settings.toml on startup.\nImportant behavior:\n\nIf the file is missing, Nova writes an embedded default config.\nIf the file exists but fails to parse as TOML, Nova overwrites it with defaults.\n\nIf you’re experimenting, keep a backup of settings.toml.\nCommand Palette\nNova includes a command palette with actions like:\n\nAsk AI\nExplain Error\nNew Tab\nSettings\n\nSee Keybindings for changing the palette shortcut.\nAI Overlay\nIf enabled, AI uses your question plus terminal context from the last command output.\nSee AI for providers, privacy notes, and troubleshooting.\n"},"55":{"title":"Quickstart > First Run","id":"quickstart/#first-run","text":""},"56":{"title":"Quickstart > Editing Settings","id":"quickstart/#editing-settings","text":""},"57":{"title":"Quickstart > Command Palette","id":"quickstart/#command-palette","text":""},"58":{"title":"Quickstart > AI Overlay","id":"quickstart/#ai-overlay","text":""},"59":{"title":"Troubleshooting","id":"troubleshooting/","text":"macOS: “Nova is damaged and can’t be opened”\nNova is not notarized. macOS Gatekeeper may block it.\nIf you installed the app bundle, you can clear the quarantine attribute:\nxattr -cr /Applications/Nova.app\n\nSettings Keep Resetting\nNova overwrites settings.toml with defaults if it fails to parse as TOML.\nIf your settings keep resetting:\n\nValidate your TOML syntax (missing quotes, stray commas, etc.)\nKeep a backup copy while editing\n\nnova ask Must Be Run Inside Nova\nnova ask is an integration command that signals the running Nova app via OSC.\nIf you run it in another terminal, you’ll get:\nerror: &#039;nova ask&#039; must be run inside Nova terminal\n\nRun it inside Nova, or use the in-app command palette action.\nAI Errors\n\nMissing key: set [ai].api_key.\nWrong model/provider: ensure model name matches the selected provider.\nProxy issues: verify [ai].base_url is correct and reachable.\n\n"},"60":{"title":"Troubleshooting > macOS: “Nova is damaged and can’t be opened”","id":"troubleshooting/#macos-nova-is-damaged-and-cant-be-opened","text":""},"61":{"title":"Troubleshooting > Settings Keep Resetting","id":"troubleshooting/#settings-keep-resetting","text":""},"62":{"title":"Troubleshooting > nova ask Must Be Run Inside Nova","id":"troubleshooting/#nova-ask-must-be-run-inside-nova","text":""},"63":{"title":"Troubleshooting > AI Errors","id":"troubleshooting/#ai-errors","text":""}},"dirtCount":0,"index":[["3",{"2":{"45":1}}],["3ecf8e",{"2":{"10":4}}],["20",{"2":{"45":1}}],["2024",{"2":{"22":1}}],["20251001",{"2":{"0":1,"10":2}}],["→",{"2":{"45":3}}],["90",{"2":{"45":1}}],["keep",{"0":{"61":1},"1":{"59":1,"61":1},"2":{"54":1,"59":3}}],["keyrings",{"2":{"32":1}}],["keys",{"2":{"10":2,"45":2}}],["keybindings",{"0":{"20":1,"45":1,"46":1,"47":1,"48":1,"49":1,"50":1,"51":1,"52":1,"53":1},"1":{"10":1,"20":1},"2":{"10":3,"27":1,"45":4,"54":1}}],["key",{"2":{"0":5,"10":4,"32":1,"59":2}}],["k",{"2":{"45":1}}],["xattr",{"2":{"59":1}}],["x07",{"2":{"40":3}}],["x1b",{"2":{"40":3}}],["8",{"0":{"44":1},"1":{"40":1,"44":1},"2":{"40":3,"45":1